	<h2>Cleaning and Care for Low-Maintenance Fences</h2>

	<h3>Vinyl Fence Cleaning Guide</h3>

	<p><strong>Basic Annual Cleaning:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Timing:</strong> Spring, after pollen season ends</li>
		<li><strong>Supplies:</strong> Garden hose, soft bristle brush, bucket, mild dish soap</li>
		<li><strong>Method:</strong> Rinse with hose, scrub with soapy water, rinse clean</li>
		<li><strong>Time required:</strong> 1-2 hours for 100 linear feet</li>
		<li><strong>Cost:</strong> $5-10 for soap and supplies</li>
	</ul>

	<p><strong>Stubborn Stain Removal:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Mold/mildew:</strong> White vinegar solution (1:1 vinegar to water)</li>
		<li><strong>Algae:</strong> Oxygen bleach (safer than chlorine bleach)</li>
		<li><strong>Grease/oil:</strong> Degreasing dish soap or automotive degreaser</li>
		<li><strong>Rust stains:</strong> Commercial rust remover safe for vinyl</li>
		<li><strong>Spray paint:</strong> Mineral spirits or graffiti remover</li>
	</ul>

	<p><strong>What to Avoid:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Abrasive cleaners:</strong> Can scratch or dull vinyl surface</li>
		<li><strong>Pressure washers on high:</strong> Can damage fence (use low pressure only)</li>
		<li><strong>Metal brushes:</strong> Scratch and gouge vinyl permanently</li>
		<li><strong>Harsh chemicals:</strong> Some solvents can discolor or damage vinyl</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Aluminum Fence Maintenance</h3>

	<p><strong>Annual Care Routine:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Wash fence:</strong> Soap and water removes dirt, environmental buildup</li>
		<li><strong>Check connections:</strong> Verify all screws and brackets tight</li>
		<li><strong>Lubricate gates:</strong> Apply silicone spray to hinges and latches</li>
		<li><strong>Inspect powder coat:</strong> Look for chips or scratches needing touch-up</li>
		<li><strong>Touch-up if needed:</strong> Use matching paint pen for minor scratches</li>
	</ul>

	<p><strong>Extending Aluminum Fence Life:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Keep sprinklers from constantly hitting fence (promotes oxidation)</li>
		<li>Trim vegetation away from fence (prevents scratching and moisture retention)</li>
		<li>Address scratches promptly (prevents aluminum oxidation in scratch)</li>
		<li>Don't lean heavy objects against fence (prevents bending)</li>
	</ul>

